title.narrative: HUMANITARIAN: STREGTHENED LEADERSHIP INTHE HUMANITARIAN SECTOR

description.narrative: UNICEF in MENA strengthens its leadership in the humanitarian sector in devising innovative ways to identify, reach and advocate for people in need in complex and high threat environments, which contributes to Cross-Sectoral Monitoring, Data And Situation Analyses, Cross-Sectoral Planning And Programme Reviews, Other Cross-Sectoral Programme Areas, Water. UNICEF aims to achieve this through Advocacy And Public Engagement, Evaluations, Research And Data, Fostering Innovation And Use Of New Technologies, Systems Strengthening And Institution Building. This contributes to the following Country Programme result: UNICEF demonstrates enhanced evidence-informed leadership and broadened partnerships to promote child rights and wellbeing across MENA.

title.narrative: UNICEF in MENA strengthens its leadership in the humanitarian sector in devising innovative ways to identify, reach and advocatefor people in need in complex and high threat environments

description.narrative: The Middle East and North Africa Regional Office (MENARO) continued to strengthen humanitarian leadership by conducting programme evaluations, mapping the cluster’s capacity and performance, increasing risk analysis, contributing to Common Country Assessments and rolling out the 2020 revised Core Commitments for Children in Humanitarian Action in 16 country offices (COs). The Regional Office (RO) collaborated with interagency coordination mechanisms to increase humanitarian predictability and accountability. The RO also strengthened partnerships with other United Nations agencies and developed a regional programme cooperation agreement with the International Federation of Red Cross and Red Crescent Societies. | Status:Partially met | As-of Date:28/03/2022
